\ flip ( array k -- ) reverses array[0..k] inclusive, in place.

variable A

\ whole array
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] to A   A 4 flip   A . cr     \ [ 5 4 3 2 1 ]

\ prefix only
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] to A   A 2 flip   A . cr     \ [ 3 2 1 4 5 ]

\ k = 0 is a no-op
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] to A   A 0 flip   A . cr     \ [ 1 2 3 4 5 ]

\ adjacent swap
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] to A   A 1 flip   A . cr     \ [ 2 1 3 4 5 ]

\ single-element array, k = 0
[ 9 ] to A   A 0 flip   A . cr             \ [ 9 ]

\ errors
[ 1 2 3 ] 3 flip       \ index out of bounds
[ 1 2 3 ] -1 flip      \ negative index
5 0 flip               \ not an array
